Hi @gagarin77!

The css rule isn't working because of the `td` has a class name of `calendTname`; and also because of [CSS specificity](https://css-tricks.com/specifics-on-css-specificity/). If you right click and inspect a cell in that column, you'll see this definition is set to center align the text

```css
#fixed-columns-table tbody td {
    /* other definitions */
    text-align: center;
}
```

Increase the CSS specificity of your definition. Maybe try something like this:

```css
#fixed-columns-table tbody td.calendTname {
  text-align:left;
}
```

